//faq item My smartphone can’t find any device for coupling with. - Ensure the same Wifi connection\n- Turn off VPN\n- Shorten the distance between devices\n- Check supported devices
My smartphone gets stuck “connecting” to couple with TV. - Restart the smartphone’s wifi and reconnect to devices.\n- Turn off the TV and unplug it for 1 minute then turn it on again.\n- Shorten the distance between your phone and the TV.
My devices could connect before, but those do not work now? If your devices could connect previously, those can be definitely connected again. You may check VPN, the same Wifi, and the distance. You even deal with the problems by restarting your devices.
It shows that my device is not supported. What should we do? This means that your device does not support the screen mirroring function.\nYou could find supported devices to be able to mirror TV.
